Perfect üëè ‚Äî that‚Äôs a clean and valid Angular 10 structure.

Let‚Äôs make sure each of those four files (app.ts, app.config.ts, app.routes.ts, app.spec.ts) are correctly written and connected, so that the app boots up without any ‚Äústandalone‚Äù, ‚Äúnot exported‚Äù, or ‚Äúmodule not found‚Äù errors.

‚∏ª

‚úÖ 1Ô∏è‚É£ app.ts ‚Äî Your Root Component

This defines the root UI container (the green sidebar + router-outlet area).

import { Component } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  templateUrl: './app.html',
  styleUrls: ['./app.css']
})
export class App {
  title = 'Travel Portal';
  sidebarOpen = false;

  toggleSidebar() {
    this.sidebarOpen = !this.sidebarOpen;
  }
}

‚úÖ Make sure you have app.html and app.css alongside this file.

‚∏ª

‚úÖ 2Ô∏è‚É£ app.routes.ts ‚Äî Routing Configuration

This defines navigation between pages.

import { Routes } from '@angular/router';
import { WelcomeComponent } from './welcome/welcome';
import { TravellComponent } from './travell/travell';
import { TravelDetailsComponent } from './travel-details/travel-details';
import { ApprovalsComponent } from './approvals/approvals';

export const routes: Routes = [
  { path: '', component: WelcomeComponent },
  { path: 'new-travel', component: TravellComponent },
  { path: 'travel-details', component: TravelDetailsComponent },
  { path: 'approvals', component: ApprovalsComponent }
];

‚úÖ Make sure each of those components exists and is not standalone.

‚∏ª

‚úÖ 3Ô∏è‚É£ app.config.ts ‚Äî Root Module (replaces app.module.ts)

This is where everything is declared and imported.

import { NgModule } from '@angular/core';
import { BrowserModule } from '@angular/platform-browser';
import { FormsModule } from '@angular/forms';
import { HttpClientModule } from '@angular/common/http';
import { RouterModule } from '@angular/router';

import { App } from './app';
import { TravellComponent } from './travell/travell';
import { ApprovalsComponent } from './approvals/approvals';
import { TravelDetailsComponent } from './travel-details/travel-details';
import { WelcomeComponent } from './welcome/welcome';
import { routes } from './app.routes';

@NgModule({
  declarations: [
    App,
    TravellComponent,
    ApprovalsComponent,
    TravelDetailsComponent,
    WelcomeComponent
  ],
  imports: [
    BrowserModule,
    FormsModule,
    HttpClientModule,
    RouterModule.forRoot(routes)
  ],
  bootstrap: [App]
})
export class AppModule {}

‚úÖ This replaces app.module.ts, so don‚Äôt create that file.

‚∏ª

‚úÖ 4Ô∏è‚É£ app.spec.ts ‚Äî Optional Test File

You can keep this minimal:

import { TestBed } from '@angular/core/testing';
import { App } from './app';

describe('App Root Component', () => {
  beforeEach(() => TestBed.configureTestingModule({ declarations: [App] }));

  it('should create the app', () => {
    const fixture = TestBed.createComponent(App);
    const app = fixture.componentInstance;
    expect(app).toBeTruthy();
  });
});


‚∏ª

‚úÖ 5Ô∏è‚É£ main.ts ‚Äî Bootstrapping Angular

import { platformBrowserDynamic } from '@angular/platform-browser-dynamic';
import { AppModule } from './app/app.config';

platformBrowserDynamic()
  .bootstrapModule(AppModule)
  .catch((err: any) => console.error(err));


‚∏ª

‚úÖ Summary of Connection Flow

main.ts
  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ bootstraps AppModule (from app.config.ts)
         ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ declares App component (from app.ts)
         ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ imports routes (from app.routes.ts)
         ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ bootstraps <app-root> in index.html


‚∏ª

If you copy these five snippets exactly into your project, your Angular 10 setup will:
	‚Ä¢	‚úÖ Recognize all components
	‚Ä¢	‚úÖ Avoid standalone errors
	‚Ä¢	‚úÖ Correctly load routes
	‚Ä¢	‚úÖ Compile cleanly without module export issues

