Perfect ‚Äî that helps a lot üëå

So your setup is Angular 10-style, but instead of the standard app.component.ts, you‚Äôre using a root file called app.ts (which exports a class named App).

That‚Äôs totally fine ‚úÖ ‚Äî we‚Äôll keep your structure as-is and make the fixes around it.

‚∏ª

üß© The Real Problem

You‚Äôre seeing:

‚ùå ‚ÄúComponent X is standalone and cannot be declared in NgModule‚Äù

because Angular thinks your components are standalone, but in Angular 10 (and in your setup),
there is no standalone mode ‚Äî all components must be declared in your main module (which is your App class in app.ts).

‚∏ª

‚úÖ Fix Summary (Step-by-Step)

Step 1 ‚Äî Edit all component .ts files

For each of these:
	‚Ä¢	travell.ts
	‚Ä¢	traveldetails.ts
	‚Ä¢	approvals.ts
	‚Ä¢	welcome.ts

Remove the line standalone: true from the @Component({}) decorator.

So for example, your travell.ts should look like this üëá

import { Component } from '@angular/core';
import { NgForm } from '@angular/forms';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-travell',
  templateUrl: './travell.html',
  styleUrls: ['./travell.css']
})
export class TravellComponent {
  // component logic here
}

‚úÖ Repeat the same change for all other components.

‚∏ª

Step 2 ‚Äî Update your app.ts (main module)

Make sure your app.ts looks like this üëá

import { NgModule } from '@angular/core';
import { BrowserModule } from '@angular/platform-browser';
import { FormsModule } from '@angular/forms';
import { HttpClientModule } from '@angular/common/http';
import { RouterModule } from '@angular/router';

import { App } from './app';  // your main class
import { TravellComponent } from './travell';
import { TravelDetailsComponent } from './traveldetails';
import { ApprovalsComponent } from './approvals';
import { WelcomeComponent } from './welcome';
import { routes } from './app.route';  // assuming this exports routes[]

@NgModule({
  declarations: [
    App,
    TravellComponent,
    TravelDetailsComponent,
    ApprovalsComponent,
    WelcomeComponent
  ],
  imports: [
    BrowserModule,
    FormsModule,
    HttpClientModule,
    RouterModule.forRoot(routes)
  ],
  bootstrap: [App]
})
export class AppModule { }


‚∏ª

Step 3 ‚Äî Make sure your main.ts bootstraps this module

import { platformBrowserDynamic } from '@angular/platform-browser-dynamic';
import { AppModule } from './app/app';

platformBrowserDynamic()
  .bootstrapModule(AppModule)
  .catch(err => console.error(err));


