Perfect üëç
You‚Äôre 100% right ‚Äî that‚Äôs a common Angular 17+ mistake that happens when we mix standalone components with the older NgModule system.

Let‚Äôs clarify and fix it once and for all üëá

‚∏ª

üß© Why You‚Äôre Seeing This Error

Error:

‚ùå Component App is standalone and cannot be declared in an NgModule.

‚öôÔ∏è What it means:

Angular now allows two ways to define components:

Type	Description
üß± NgModule-based (older style)	Uses @NgModule + declarations array (ex: AppModule)
‚ö° Standalone components (Angular 15+)	Uses @Component({ standalone: true }) and imported directly into routes

You cannot mix both at the same time.

‚∏ª

‚úÖ Two Ways to Fix It

Option 1 (Recommended for Angular 17+):

üëâ Make everything standalone ‚Äî no AppModule at all.
We‚Äôll use app.ts (standalone root) and routes properly.

‚∏ª

üß± Fix Steps ‚Äî Stand-alone Component Setup

Let‚Äôs go file by file üëá

‚∏ª

1Ô∏è‚É£ app.ts ‚Äî your root setup

Replace your existing app.ts with this:

import { Component } from '@angular/core';
import { RouterOutlet } from '@angular/router';
import { CommonModule } from '@angular/common';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [RouterOutlet, CommonModule],
  templateUrl: './app.html',
  styleUrls: ['./app.css']
})
export class App {}

‚úÖ This defines your root as a standalone component (no AppModule needed).

‚∏ª

2Ô∏è‚É£ app.routes.ts

import { Routes } from '@angular/router';
import { WelcomeComponent } from './welcome';
import { TravellComponent } from './travell';
import { TravelDetailsComponent } from './travel-details';
import { ApprovalsComponent } from './approvals';

export const routes: Routes = [
  { path: '', component: WelcomeComponent },
  { path: 'new-travel', component: TravellComponent },
  { path: 'travel-details', component: TravelDetailsComponent },
  { path: 'approvals', component: ApprovalsComponent }
];


‚∏ª

3Ô∏è‚É£ main.ts

Make sure this looks like:

import { bootstrapApplication } from '@angular/platform-browser';
import { App } from './app/app';
import { provideRouter } from '@angular/router';
import { routes } from './app/app.routes';
import { importProvidersFrom } from '@angular/core';
import { HttpClientModule } from '@angular/common/http';

bootstrapApplication(App, {
  providers: [
    provideRouter(routes),
    importProvidersFrom(HttpClientModule)
  ]
}).catch(err => console.error(err));


‚∏ª

4Ô∏è‚É£ Each Component (like travell.ts, approvals.ts, etc.)

At the top of every component (travell, travel-details, approvals, welcome),
make sure the decorator looks like this üëá

@Component({
  selector: 'app-travell',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [CommonModule, FormsModule],
  templateUrl: './travell.html',
  styleUrls: ['./travell.css']
})
export class TravellComponent { ... }

‚úÖ Add standalone: true
‚úÖ Add imports: [CommonModule, FormsModule]

For each component ‚Äî
use CommonModule (for *ngIf, *ngFor, etc.)
and FormsModule (for [(ngModel)], forms, etc.)

‚∏ª

5Ô∏è‚É£ Delete Any Old Module File

If you still have something like app.module.ts, delete it.
Standalone components don‚Äôt use modules anymore.

‚∏ª

After this

Run:

ng serve

‚úÖ The error ‚ÄúComponent is standalone cannot be declared in NgModule‚Äù will disappear.
‚úÖ All routes (home, new travel, approvals, travel details) will load perfectly.

‚∏ª

Would you like me to send you the updated decorator blocks for all 4 components (travell, travel-details, approvals, welcome) so you can copy them directly without missing imports?


















import { Component, OnInit } from '@angular/core';
import { TravelService } from '../services/travel';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-approvals',
  templateUrl: './approvals.html',
  styleUrls: ['./approvals.css']
})
export class ApprovalsComponent implements OnInit {

  approvalsList: any[] = [];

  constructor(private travelService: TravelService) {}

  ngOnInit(): void {
    this.loadApprovals();
  }

  loadApprovals(): void {
    this.approvalsList = this.travelService.getAllTravels();
  }

  approve(travel: any): void {
    const uid = String(travel.uid); // ‚úÖ Convert UID to string to fix type issue
    this.travelService.updateStatus(uid, 'Approved');

    // Update status instantly in the approvals table
    travel.status = 'Approved';
  }

  reject(travel: any): void {
    const uid = String(travel.uid); // ‚úÖ Convert UID to string to fix type issue
    this.travelService.updateStatus(uid, 'Rejected');

    // Update status instantly in the approvals table
    travel.status = 'Rejected';
  }
}







import { Injectable } from '@angular/core';
import { HttpClient } from '@angular/common/http';
import { Observable, of } from 'rxjs';

@Injectable({
  providedIn: 'root'
})
export class TravelService {
  
  private baseUrl = 'http://localhost:8080/api/travel'; // üëà Your Spring Boot base URL

  // Store submitted travels (for Travel Details & Approvals tables)
  private travelList: any[] = [];

  constructor(private http: HttpClient) {}

  // ---- Dropdown Fetch Methods ----
  getDomains(): Observable<string[]> {
    // Expected backend endpoint: /api/travel/domains
    return this.http.get<string[]>(`${this.baseUrl}/domains`);
  }

  getClusters(): Observable<string[]> {
    // Expected backend endpoint: /api/travel/clusters
    return this.http.get<string[]>(`${this.baseUrl}/clusters`);
  }

  getSubClusters(): Observable<string[]> {
    // Expected backend endpoint: /api/travel/sub-clusters
    return this.http.get<string[]>(`${this.baseUrl}/sub-clusters`);
  }

  getCluster1List(): Observable<string[]> {
    // Expected backend endpoint: /api/travel/cluster1
    return this.http.get<string[]>(`${this.baseUrl}/cluster1`);
  }

  getHods(): Observable<string[]> {
    // Expected backend endpoint: /api/travel/hods
    return this.http.get<string[]>(`${this.baseUrl}/hods`);
  }

  getCities(): Observable<string[]> {
    // Expected backend endpoint: /api/travel/cities
    return this.http.get<string[]>(`${this.baseUrl}/cities`);
  }

  // ---- Add Travel Record ----
  addTravel(travelData: any): void {
    // Store locally (for now)
    this.travelList.push({ ...travelData, status: 'Approval Pending' });

    // Optional: send to backend (uncomment if backend is ready)
    // return this.http.post(`${this.baseUrl}/submit`, travelData).subscribe();

    console.log('‚úÖ Travel added:', travelData);
  }

  // ---- Get All Travels ----
  getAllTravels(): any[] {
    return this.travelList;
  }

  // ---- Update Travel Status ----
  updateStatus(uid: string, newStatus: string): void {
    const travel = this.travelList.find(t => t.uid === uid);
    if (travel) {
      travel.status = newStatus;
    }
  }
}











import { Component, OnInit } from '@angular/core';
import { NgForm } from '@angular/forms';
import { TravelService } from '../services/travel';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-travell',
  templateUrl: './travell.html',
  styleUrls: ['./travell.css']
})
export class TravellComponent implements OnInit {
  
  // Form model
  travel = {
    uid: '',
    name: '',
    lineManager: '',
    domain: '',
    cluster: '',
    subCluster: '',
    cluster1: '',
    hod: '',
    travelType: '',
    originCity: '',
    destinationCity: '',
    startDate: '',
    endDate: '',
    travelClass: '',
    type: '',
    purpose: ''
  };

  // Dropdown lists populated from backend
  domains: string[] = [];
  clusters: string[] = [];
  subClusters: string[] = [];
  cluster1List: string[] = [];
  hodList: string[] = [];
  cities: string[] = [];

  // Flags
  submitted = false;

  constructor(private travelService: TravelService) {}

  ngOnInit(): void {
    // Fetch dropdown values from backend YAMLs
    this.travelService.getDomains().subscribe(data => this.domains = data);
    this.travelService.getClusters().subscribe(data => this.clusters = data);
    this.travelService.getSubClusters().subscribe(data => this.subClusters = data);
    this.travelService.getCluster1List().subscribe(data => this.cluster1List = data);
    this.travelService.getHods().subscribe(data => this.hodList = data);
    this.travelService.getCities().subscribe(data => this.cities = data);
  }

  // ‚úÖ Proper onSubmit function
  onSubmit(form: NgForm): void {
    if (form.invalid) {
      alert('‚ö†Ô∏è Please fill all required fields before submitting.');
      return;
    }

    this.submitted = true;

    // Save new travel record
    this.travelService.addTravel(this.travel);

    alert('‚úÖ Travel request submitted successfully!');
    
    // Reset form
    form.resetForm();
  }
}









import { NgModule, Component } from '@angular/core';
import { BrowserModule } from '@angular/platform-browser';
import { CommonModule } from '@angular/common';
import { FormsModule, ReactiveFormsModule } from '@angular/forms';
import { RouterModule } from '@angular/router';

import { TravellComponent } from './travell/travell';
import { TravelDetailsComponent } from './travel-details/travel-details';
import { ApprovalsComponent } from './approvals/approvals';
import { WelcomeComponent } from './welcome/welcome';
import { TravelService } from './services/travel';

/* -----------------------------------------------------------
   Root Component (Main App)
------------------------------------------------------------ */
@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  templateUrl: './app.html',
  styleUrls: ['./app.css']
})
export class App {
  title = 'Travel Portal';
}

/* -----------------------------------------------------------
   App Module Configuration
------------------------------------------------------------ */
@NgModule({
  declarations: [
    App,
    TravellComponent,
    TravelDetailsComponent,
    ApprovalsComponent,
    WelcomeComponent
  ],
  imports: [
    BrowserModule,
    CommonModule,              // ‚úÖ Enables *ngIf, *ngFor, ngClass, etc.
    FormsModule,               // ‚úÖ Enables ngForm
    ReactiveFormsModule,       // ‚úÖ Enables FormBuilder
    RouterModule.forRoot([
      { path: '', component: WelcomeComponent },
      { path: 'new-travel', component: TravellComponent },
      { path: 'travel-details', component: TravelDetailsComponent },
      { path: 'approvals', component: ApprovalsComponent }
    ])
  ],
  providers: [TravelService],
  bootstrap: [App]
})
export class AppModule {}





Perfect bro üî• ‚Äî these errors are 100% Angular module/import related, not logic issues.
They happen when we use Angular structural directives (*ngIf, *ngFor, ngClass, ngForm)
without importing the right modules in your app setup.

Let‚Äôs fix all of them step-by-step and cleanly üëá

‚∏ª

‚ö†Ô∏è Errors You‚Äôre Seeing

Error	Root Cause
NgIf used but not imported	Missing CommonModule import
NgFor used but not imported	Missing CommonModule import
ngClass not a known property	Missing CommonModule import
No directive found with exportAs ngForm	Missing FormsModule or ReactiveFormsModule import
Expected 0 arguments but got 1	Usually from incorrect FormBuilder.group() or service method call


